From: knsol <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] fix: fs_unlink stale /SD:/a01.txt at boot

Reproduced regression: patch 0038 first run had fs_open failures = 0
(96 successful writes), but every subsequent boot has fs_open failures
= 100% with -ENOENT — even with the same firmware. The SD card's
prior /SD:/a01.txt entry is in a half-committed state from fs_close
-EIO during the previous run; the FAT entry exists but Zephyr/FATFS
can't open it.

fs_unlink at mount removes the stale entry so write_to_file's
fs_open(FS_O_CREATE) creates a fresh one.
---
diff --git a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c
index 719b0a2..ad07db1 100644
--- a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c
+++ b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c
@@ -80,10 +80,16 @@ int mount_sd_card(void)
     } else {
         LOG_ERR("f_mount failed: %d", res);
         return -1;
     }
 
+    /* Patch 0040: nuke stale a01.txt at boot to recover from prior
+     * half-committed FAT entries (fs_close -EIO during normal writes
+     * leaves the file unrecoverable on next boot). */
+    int unlink_ret = fs_unlink("/SD:/a01.txt");
+    LOG_INF("boot: fs_unlink(/SD:/a01.txt) = %d", unlink_ret);
+
     res = fs_mkdir("/SD:/audio");
 
     if (res == FR_OK) {
         LOG_INF("audio directory created successfully");
         initialize_audio_file(1);
